   {:e #blake3 "2893d48d26d0277d908cca963d1814ab92052b91c3fe562b48c2899d06844162" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Signal module (1,465 LOC) has 26 unit tests but no integration or E2E tests. Alert fatigue detection (suppressing repeated signals) has never been tested in realistic multi-command context. RATIONALE: INV-SIGNAL-001. Signal routing affects guidance quality. If alert fatigue fails, agents get spammed with redundant warnings, wasting token budget. APPROACH: E2E script: (1) Initialize store. (2) Run braid status 5 times rapidly. (3) Verify: first status shows full signal set, subsequent calls show dampened/suppressed signals. (4) Wait simulated interval, run again — verify signals re-emerge after cooldown. (5) Inject a new divergence signal between calls — verify it appears despite dampening of old signals. FAILURE DIAGNOSTICS: Log: signal_type, suppression_count, cooldown_remaining, expected_visible, actual_visible. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Rapid repeated calls show signal suppression. (B) New signals penetrate dampening. (C) Cooldown expiry restores signals. FILE: scripts/e2e_signal_routing.sh" :op :assert}
